# Redirects (Netlify format).
# The site isn't live yet, so these are precautionary — they only matter
# if the old URLs were ever indexed or linked externally.

# Canonical host: force www → apex (Netlify also needs the primary
# domain set to scalebizmarketing.com in Site settings → Domain).
https://www.scalebizmarketing.com/* https://scalebizmarketing.com/:splat 301!
http://www.scalebizmarketing.com/*  https://scalebizmarketing.com/:splat 301!

# Clean URLs: strip the .html extension so the address bar / indexed URL
# is the page name only (e.g. /service, not /service.html). The `!` forces
# the redirect — without it Netlify serves the physical .html file instead
# of redirecting. The extensionless target is still served from the same
# file (Netlify maps /service → service.html), so there is no loop.
/index.html          /               301!
/about.html          /about          301!
/service.html        /service        301!
/case-study.html     /case-study     301!
/contact.html        /contact        301!
/blog/index.html     /blog/          301!
/legal/privacy.html  /legal/privacy  301!
/legal/terms.html    /legal/terms    301!
/legal/cookies.html  /legal/cookies  301!

# Legal pages moved into /legal/ (2026-07-13) — now point at clean URLs
/privacy.html   /legal/privacy   301
/terms.html     /legal/terms     301
/cookies.html   /legal/cookies   301
/privacy        /legal/privacy   301
/terms          /legal/terms     301
/cookies        /legal/cookies   301

# Blog rebuilt at /blog/ (was blogs.html)
/blogs.html     /blog/                301
/blogs          /blog/                301

# Keep non-site files out of the public web root. The `!` forces the
# 404 even though the file physically exists in the deploy (Netlify
# serves real files over un-forced redirects). Backend source, DB
# schema, and internal briefs must not be downloadable.
/supabase/*                 /404.html   404!
/prompt.md                  /404.html   404!
/folder_structure_logo.md   /404.html   404!
/.claude/*                  /404.html   404!
